replyText: Thanks for the feedback! The timezone issue is definitely something we need to work on. I'll definitely at it to our to-do list.

text: Amazingly precise. I don't understand half of it. But I do understand the other half, so that's good. Does that render my participation / results pointless? Or is that better than nothing?
replyText: Thanks for the feedback, we're definitely working to make things more intuitive. Responding when you can is definitely better than nothing! You can also set the frequency of the prompts in the upper right hand corner if it feels like it's too often.

text: Love it. There is one downfall with the sleep tracking. I don't like my phone plugged in all night and just because it's plugged in doesn't mean I am asleep. I Would prefer a button  to push when I am actually laying down with my eyes closed and trying to sleep. Not laying in bed reading, watching tv, or dealing with anxiety. Then if I forget to plug it back in or out of habit unplug it because the charged light is on, AND the tracking never worked. Also, I have insomnia so my aleep schedules vary, and having a sleep schedule set based on the weekends versus the weekdays isn't very effective. Also would be helpful to alter the survey questions some. either way I am enjoying the app.
replyText: Thanks for the feedback! We do have a manual sleep mode, which allows you to manually start and stop sleep (this can be enabled in the upper left settings menu). It sounds like this may be something that would work better for you.

We're working on an update that should be released in the next few days to fix the heart rate, sleep, and steps. See moodtriggers.com for more help.
